Description: Early 2000s “Ferden Nocaster” Rare Custom Vintage. Pure fire. Stratocaster Style expert built partscaster. What in the world?! Out of this world vintage Strat sound. Like the old school biting blues, Hendrix solo fast fretboard, customizable in every way imaginable sound. Olympic white. Check. Lava red pickguard. Check. Vintage custom pickups. Check. Warmoth 6100 (vintage) Brazilian rosewood fretboard with birds eye maple neck. Check. Such a beauty and a perfect addition to the partscaster purist connection. Beautifully maintained and reconditioned in 2019 and tuned up at the Philly Famous Dipinto guitars. Fire. Pickups: $800+ value (not to mention rare) Van Zandt Vintage Plus Strat 6.7 Van Zandt Vintage Plus Strat 6.7 Lindy Fralin Pickups Vintage High Output Middle (8.67) Neck: $500+ (rare vintage) Warmoth 6100 Brazilian Rosewood and Birdseye Maple (so lightly flamed) Self Locking Chrome Tuners Custom build with vintage sounds and old school fat Strat tone. Features an Olympic white 70s Japanese style Squier Strat body, oldschool Warmoth neck, locking chrome tuners, Custom wired Van Zandt Vintage Plus Strat neck and mid pickups with a Lindy Fralin high output reverse middle bridge pickup, standard Strat bridge and Wammy bar. Get at this. Lava hot and beautiful warm fat steamy tones.
Title: Stratocaster Style Custom Vintage Partscaster
